t Swing access, so the second test failed immediately when `SwingUtilities` touched the toolkit.\\n\\n## Codex log assessment\\n\\nThe Codex metadata-fix log shows it kept chasing JDK Swing/AWT internals for this GUI path, adding metadata for classes such as `java.awt.GraphicsEnvironment` and `sun.awt.SunToolkit`, but the final Gradle failure still ended in X11 toolkit initialization errors (`sun.awt.X11.XErrorHandlerUtil` / `sun.awt.X11.XToolkit`).\\n\\nThat indicates the remaining problem is not unresolved library metadata for `com.mchange`; it is an unsupported or unsuitable native Swing/X11 execution path for this generated test.\\n\\n## Intervention applied\\n\\nRemoved the generated test file:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.2.15/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated suite still exercises real, non-GUI library behaviors and passed after removing only this Swing/X11-specific test. Preserving the remaining generated tests and support keeps coverage for the metadata-relevant code paths that do work in native image, while dropping only the platform-dependent GUI scenario that is not a reliable metadata signal for this library.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter removing `PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`, the coordinate passed with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.2.15 --stacktrace`\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:1904:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:1945:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.2.15\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe generated support failed only in the native test run, and the failures came from the generated Swing-based test `PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest`, not from unresolved `com.mchange` library metadata.\\n\\nBoth failing test methods instantiate `com.mchange.v2.beans.swing.PropertyBoundTextField`. In the native image run, that triggers JDK AWT/Swing native initialization and fails inside `java.awt.Component.initIDs()` with `java.lang.NoSuchFieldError: java.awt.Component.isPacked`. The second failure is then just a follow-on `NoClassDefFoundError` because `PropertyBoundTextField` could not finish class initialization.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldSyncsInitialAndUpdatedBeanValue()`\\n\\n- Failure: `java.lang.NoSuchFieldError: java.awt.Component.isPacked`\\n- Root cause: non-metadata-related native-image desktop/JNI initialization issue in JDK AWT/Swing.\\n- Why this is not library metadata: the failure occurs in `java.desktop` while initializing `java.awt.Component`, before any missing `com.mchange` reachability entry is reported. This is a JDK desktop support problem, not missing library metadata for `mchange-commons-java`.\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldAppliesUserChangesBackToBean()`\\n\\n- Failure: `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class com.mchange.v2.beans.swing.PropertyBoundTextField`\\n- Root cause: same underlying AWT/Swing initialization failure as above.\\n- Why this is not library metadata: this is only the cascading error after the first test already failed class initialization.\\n\\n## Intervention\\n\\nRemoved the generated test file:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.2.15/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated coverage is still valuable and passed after removing the Swing-only test. It continues to validate native-image behavior for the library's reflection, proxies, serialization, naming, logging, thread-pool, collection, JDBC, XML, and codegen utilities.\\n\\nRemoving the single Swing/AWT-native test avoids chasing JDK desktop internals in library metadata while preserving the broader generated support that does exercise `mchange-commons-java` functionality successfully.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter removing `PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`, the targeted run succeeded:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.2.15 --stacktrace`\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:1967:    \"status\": \"failure\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:1994:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2054:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2119:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2207:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2272:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2337:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2402:      \"dynami