e-image explicitly applying that test reachability file.\\n- Even with that registration present, runtime still threw the same `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from the deserialization path inside `ObjectInputStream` / `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance`.\\n\\nConclusion: this is a current native-image limitation/behavior for this serialization-based construction path, not an unfixed metadata omission in this repository.\\n\\n### `ObjectStreamClassInstantiatorTest`\\n\\nFailure: native image still rejected reflective invocation of:\\n\\n- `org_objenesis.objenesis.ObjectStreamClassInstantiatorTest$NonSerializableParent()`\\n\\nWhy this is not a metadata gap:\\n\\n- The exact constructor entry was already present in the generated test reachability metadata.\\n- The failure persisted after a clean native-image rebuild that applied that metadata file.\\n- The exception still came from the JDK serialization allocation path invoked by `ObjectStreamClassInstantiator`.\\n\\nConclusion: same native-image serialization-constructor limitation, not missing library metadata.\\n\\n### `SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest#followsSerializationConstructionRulesForSerializableTypes`\\n\\nFailure: native image still rejected reflective invocation of:\\n\\n- `org_objenesis.objenesis.SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest$NonSerializableParent()`\\n\\nWhy this is not a metadata gap:\\n\\n- Codex had already added the exact constructor registration suggested by the runtime.\\n- The Codex log also shows that a separate `ReflectionFactory` metadata issue was fixed earlier; the remaining failure narrowed down to the serialization constructor invocation itself.\\n- After a clean rebuild, the same constructor-registration error still happened through `SunReflectionFactorySerializationInstantiator`.\\n\\nConclusion: this is also a native-image limitation around serialization-style parent-constructor invocation, not an unresolved metadata entry.\\n\\n## Action taken\\n\\nRemoved the generated failing coverage:\\n\\n- deleted `tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/3.2/src/test/java/org_objenesis/objenesis/ObjectInputStreamInstantiatorTest.java`\\n- deleted `tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/3.2/src/test/java/org_objenesis/objenesis/ObjectStreamClassInstantiatorTest.java`\\n- removed `followsSerializationConstructionRulesForSerializableTypes()` and its serialization-only helper classes from `tests/src/org.objenesis/objenesis/3.2/src/test/java/org_objenesis/objenesis/SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest.java`\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still provides meaningful coverage for Objenesis 3.2:\\n\\n- the native test suite still validates the supported constructor-bypass behavior that works in native image\\n- helper and strategy coverage (`ClassUtils`, `ConstructorInstantiator`, `DelegatingToExoticInstantiator`, `SingleInstantiatorStrategy`, `UnsafeFactoryInstantiator`) remains intact\\n- `SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest#createsInstancesWithoutRunningTheTargetConstructor` still validates the non-serialization ReflectionFactory-based path that succeeds in native image\\n- Android/GCJ/PERC tests are assumption-guarded and abort intentionally outside their applicable runtime/platform conditions, so they are not part of the failure\\n\\nAfter removing only the serialization-path tests above, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.objenesis:objenesis:3.2 --stacktrace` succeeds.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8660:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8748:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8808:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8868:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8919:    \"library\": \"org.osgi:org.osgi.service.serviceloader:1.0.0\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8928:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8959:    \"status\": \"failure\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:8987:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9052:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9093:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe generated Lombok support originally failed in native-image because the test set mixed two kinds of problems:\\n\\n- **recoverable shadow-launch support gaps** that Codex partially fixed for `AgentDynamicAccessTest` and `AnnotationProcessorHiderAnnotationProcessorDynamicAccessTest`, and\\n- **non-metadata native-image/classloading limitations** in the remaining launcher and shadow-loader tests.\\n\\nI removed the non-metadata tests that still failed and kept the generated support that is still valid. After removing those tests, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace` passed.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### 1. `AgentDynamicAccessTest`\\n- **Failure from the provided Gradle excerpt:** `NoSuchMethodException` for `lombok.launch.Agent.premain(String, Instrumentation)`.\\n- **Assessment:** metadata/support gap, not a reason to remove the test.\\n- **What happened:** the generated support around Lombok's shadow-launch path was initially incomplete, so the reflective launch path was not available during the native test.\\n- **Outcome:** Codex's follow-up support changes were sufficient here. The test now passes, so it was preserved.\\n\\n### 2. `AnnotationProcessorHiderAnnotationProcessorDynamicAccessTest`\\n- **Failure from the provided Gradle excerpt:** `ClassNotFoundException` for `lombok.core.AnnotationProcessor`.\\n- **Assessment:** metadata/support gap, not a reason to remove the test.\\n- **What happened:** Lombok's annotation processor wrapper depends on shadow-loaded classes/resources. The initial generation did not provide enough support for that path.\\n- **Outcome:** Codex's follow-up support changes were sufficient here. The test now passes, so it was preserved.\\n\\n### 3. `MainDynamicAccessTest`\\n- **Remaining native failure after Codex follow-up:** `ClassNotFoundException: lombok.bytecode.PoolConstantsApp`.\\n- **Assessment:** **not** a reachability-metadata.json problem.\\n- **Root cause:** this test exercises Lombok's SPI-driven shadow class loading for launcher apps. `lombok.bytecode.PoolConstantsApp` is expected to be discovered and loaded through Lombok's `.SCL.lombok` shadow mechanism, but native-image still does not make that path behave like the regular JVM classpath loader.\\n- **Action:** removed the test.\\n\\n### 4. `PatchFixesHiderUtilDynamicAccessTest`\\n- **Remaining native failure after Codex follow-up:** `ClassNotFoundException: lombok.core.Version` from `PatchFixesHider$Util.shadowLoadClass(...)`.\\n- **Assessment:** **not** a reachability-metadata.json problem.\\n- **Root cause:** this test directly depends on Lombok's shadow loader being able to materialize shadow-only classes from `.SCL.lombok` resources inside native-image. That is a classloading/runtime limitation of this generated scenario, not missing reachability metadata in `metadata/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n- **Action:** removed the test.\\n\\n### 5. `ShadowClassLoaderDynamicAccessTest`\\n- **Remaining native failure after Codex follow-up:** `ClassNotFoundException: org_projectlombok.lombok.LombokLaunchTestSupport`.\\n- **Assessment:** **not** a reachability-metadata.json problem.\\n- **Root cause:** the test expects JVM-style custom class loader delegation/definition behavior from `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoader`. In the native executable, that expectation does not hold even for the test support class itself, so this is a native-image/classloader behavior mismatch rather than missing metadata.\\n- **Action:** removed the test.\\n\\n## Removed tests\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/MainDynamicAccessTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/PatchFixesHiderUtilDynamicAccessTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/ShadowClassLoaderDynamicAccessTest.java`\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe surviving support still validates real Lombok native-image behavior that matters:\\n\\n- `AgentDynamicAccessTest` verifies the agent entry path can delegate through Lombok's launcher path in native-image.\\n- `AnnotationProcessorHiderAnnotationProcessorDynamicAccessTest` verifies the annotation-processor wrapper can still construct and initialize the wrapped processor.\\n- The added shadow-override test support/resources are still useful because they are required by the passing preserved tests.\\n\\nIn other words, the remaining generated support is not scaffold-only; it still exercises meaningful Lombok launch and annotation-processor behavior, and the removed tests were the ones blocked by native-image shadow-classloader limitations rather than missing metadata.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9122:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9163:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.22\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nCodex had already fixed the metadata-related failures for `org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.22`. The remaining native test failures were all non-metadata issues, so I removed only the generated tests that exercised those unsupported behaviors.\\n\\nRemoved generated tests:\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.22/src/test/java/lombok/launch/AgentTest.java`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsResourcesFromShadowAwareParentClasspath`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#skipsShadowEntriesWhenOverridesAreConfigured`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#reusesAlreadyLoadedClassesAndHandlesConcurrentDuplicateDefinitions`\\n\\n## Root cause of each removed failure\\n\\n### `AgentTest#premainInvokesShadowLoadedAgentLauncher`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test fails with:\\n- `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Unknown protocol: resource:/lombok/launch/Agent.class`\\n\\nLombok's agent path goes through `lombok.patcher.ClassRootFinder`, which expects a class location URL that behaves like a normal jar/file URL. Inside the native test image it receives a `resource:/...` URL instead, so the Eclipse patcher path aborts before any metadata lookup is relevant.\\n\\n### `AgentTest#agentmainInvokesShadowLoadedAgentLauncherAndRequestsReload`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThis fails for the same reason as `premain`: the agent bootstrap logic depends on URL/protocol handling that is different inside Native Image, and it dies on `resource:/...` before metadata could help.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsResourcesFromShadowAwareParentClasspath`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test expects JVM-style discovery of temp-dir parent resources and shadow entries via `ShadowClassLoader#getResources(...)`. In the native executable, those runtime-created parent resources are not enumerated the same way, so the expected resource list is empty. This is a resource-loading/runtime-behavior mismatch, not missing reachability metadata.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#skipsShadowEntriesWhenOverridesAreConfigured`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThis is the same family of issue as the previous test: it depends on JVM resource lookup behavior across runtime-created parent class loaders and override directories. In Native Image the expected shadow resource is not found, so the assertion fails. No missing reflection/resource registration error is involved.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#reusesAlreadyLoadedClassesAndHandlesConcurrentDuplicateDefinitions`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test intentionally defines the same predefined class through multiple `ShadowClassLoader` instances. Native Image reports:\\n- `UnsupportedFeatureError: A predefined class can be loaded (defined) at runtime only once by a single class loader.`\\n\\nThat is an explicit Native Image limitation around predefined/runtime-defined classes, not a metadata gap.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is still useful and should stay in place because the surviving tests continue to validate real Lombok native behavior:\\n- `AnnotationProcessorHiderAnnotationProcessorTest` proves the shadow-loaded annotation processor path works with the generated metadata.\\n- `MainTest` proves `lombok.launch.Main` can still delegate to the shadow-loaded core main class inside Native Image.\\n- `PatchFixesHiderUtilTest` still exercises Lombok's reflective utility path.\\n- `ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsClassesFromPrependedParents` still covers supported shadow class loading behavior.\\n\\nThe generated test resources under `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.22/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/` are therefore still needed by the tests that remain.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata tests, the coordinate passes:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.22`\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9192:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9246:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9300:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9360:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9425:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9479:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9544:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9602:    \"status\": \"failure\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2387-86891af9/sc